---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About, political stylometry">
  <article class="container">
    <header class="article-hero">
      <h1>About this project</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        An independent data analysis with no connection to any political
        party or media organisation.
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>Why?</h2>
    <p>
      The standard election compass asks parties what they think. This
      project starts from what parties actually do, and how they
      justify it, and how that compares to what they wrote in their
      manifestos. That angle has been missing from the Swedish
      election-compass tradition.
    </p>

    <h2>Is this journalism?</h2>
    <p>
      Closer to analysis. Everything is based on reproducible methods
      over public data. No party interviews, no surveys, no subjective
      judgements beyond those required to classify topics and word
      choices, all openly documented in the code.
    </p>

    <h2>Who's behind it?</h2>
    <p>
      An independent developer. Comments and corrections are welcome
      via
      <a href="https://github.com/freol35241/ps-sverige/issues">GitHub issues</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>What's not included?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Decisions taken outside the Riksdag chamber (government,
      agencies, EU votes).</li>
      <li>Municipal and regional politics.</li>
      <li>Questions that haven't yet been voted on during the current
      mandate.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
